[h3]Maximum Capacity[/h3]
The Maximum Capacity of a creature's belly is twice the listed Belly Capacity.

[h2]Stomach DC[/h2]
A predator's Stomach DC is 10 + the Pred's Proficiency Modifier and Constitution Modifier.

[h2]Devouring[/h2]
Any creature may make a [b]Devour[/b] attempt as an Action, or as an included feature with any Weapon or Natural Weapon that has the [b]Devour[/b] property (including Unarmed Strike). In order to do so they must be within 5 ft of their prey and make a contested vore roll against their prey. This roll is a 1d20 plus Strength or Dexterity modifier, adjusted by the Size Difference and optionally the Full Bellies table below.

Bellied prey have a movement speed of 0, are in darkness and have total cover from creatures and attacks from outside of the Predator.
[h3]Applying Size Difference[/h3]
Larger Preds have bonuses to their Devour Attempts relative to smaller creatures
[table]
[tr]
[th]Size Difference[/th]
[th]Modifier[/th]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]Per size class larger than prey[/td]
[td]+5[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]Same Size[/td]
[td]- 2[/td]
[/tr]
[tr]
[td]Per size class smaller than prey[/td]
[td]- 5[/td]
[/tr]
[/table]
[h3]Optional Rule: Full Bellies & Devouring[/h3]
Once a Pred reaches 100% stomach capacity, Devour Attempts toward their Maximum Belly Capacity begin to take increasingly large maluses to represent the difficulty of stuffing additional prey into an already packed stomach.
[table]
[tr]
[th]% Stomach Capacity[/th]
[th]Modifier[/th]
[/tr]
